metadata.name: I know this road
metadata.description:
I know this road like the back of my hand. I could travel it with my eyes closed.
I know its meanderings and its faults, and how its wind blows.

I know this road and its dreamy trees, where the birds sing songs of doubts. Will it get better? Will you be able to breathe?

I know this road and all its stones. A pathway to a place where nothing is as it seems. Will I get there? Or is it beyond my dreams?

But, I know this road, its color, and its breeze, its unending windings that force and displace——that pushes you to a new path where new  learning begins.
